=Bio=


Benjamin Mako Hill is an technology and intellectual property
researcher, activist, and consultant. He is currently working full
time on research into asynchronous collaboration technologies as a
graduate researcher at the MIT Media Laboratory in the Electronic
Publishing Group. He has been an leader, developer, and contributor
to the Free and Open Source Software (FOSS) community for more than
a decade as part of the Debian and Ubuntu projects.


Benjamin Mako Hill can be contacted at mako@atdot.cc


